  "text": "Shin et al. [CITATION_1] proposed a graph-based approach for detecting persistent topics (PT) from Microposts, which correspond to topics of long-term, steady interest to a user. For their graph based approach they introduced two novel scoring functions that measure the properties inherent to PT terms: regularity and topicality. They allow to distinguish between terms that represent persistent topics, and terms which appear in static documents. Experimental results showed that this approach outperformed other existing alternatives (including LDA and keyword extraction models).",
